Esophagus (or esophageal) cancer starts in the esophagus. To understand this type of cancer, it helps to know about the normal esophagus and what it does. The esophagus The esophagus is a muscular tube that connects the throat to the stomach. It is behind the windpipe (trachea) and in front of the spine.n some people, acid can escape from the stomach into the lower part of the esophagus. This is called gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), or just reflux. In many people, reflux causes symptoms such as heartburn or chest pain. In some, though, reflux doesnât cause any symptoms.
